OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHumans understand wild ape 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Flanguage                   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Humans understand the "signs" or       
OL,6, gestures wild chimps and bonobos use to
OL,7, communicate with one another.          
OL,9,FThat is the conclusion of a video-based
OL,10,Fstudy in which volunteers translated   
OL,11,Fape gestures. It was carried out by    
OL,12,Fresearchers at St Andrews University.  
OL,14,FIt suggests that the last common       
OL,15,Fancestor we shared with chimps used    
OL,16,Fsimilar gestures, and that these were a
OL,17,F"starting point" for our language.     
OL,19,FThe findings are published in the      
OL,20,Fscientific journal PLOS Biology.       
